input: Objective: Access a bookmarked page in Chrome
output:
To access a bookmarked page in Google Chrome, follow these steps:

1. Open Chrome on your computer.
2. On the top-left corner of the screen, click on the three horizontal lines (also known as the "hamburger" icon) to open the menu.
3. Inside the menu, go to the "Bookmarks" section and select it. This will display a list of all your bookmarked pages.
4. Find the page you want to access in the list and click on its name or thumbnail image. The browser will navigate to that bookmark.

If you have any specific bookmarks or shortcuts, this method should help you quickly access them.
